Please don’t disparage this man.  He’s doing the best he can and we don’t know the circumstances.
.
Be honest, how many of you have done this?  I have, though its been 20 years since I had to install housewrap off ladders.  I got pretty good at installing it without wrinkles up that high, but I hated it.
.
We installed housewrap on walls 2nd story and up before lifting bcause its easier and safer.  Back in 2009 we switched to using Zip System and quickly realized how superior wood structural panel +wrb+taped seams is.  Faster, safer, air barrier, easier to QC, easier to train, fewer steps.  When you price the difference in your area, you have to take into account all the costs, not just materials costs.  
.
As @risingerbuild said “housewrap is dead”.  I say “good riddance”.  
.

Back to Basics. Lay out studs to land over joists. This is best structurally and keeps MEP from shedding tears.
.
Building Science Corp has a great article on O. V. E. framing (some call it Advanced Framing). We prefer to call it Rational Framing. Basically, remove what isn't actually NEEDED.
.
Sometimes we frame 12" oc with double studs because that's NEEDED, other times 24" oc because that's what's NEEDED.
.
.
Our structural engineer was contracted to run the calcs on an old building locally to see if it could be used as apartments. The floor spanned 20' with true 2"x4" 0" oc. That's right they were ganged together pre- WWII and it calc'd out. Imagine a glulam on its side, "early mass timber" .

Remember the load tables are based on testing.

Installing top flange hangers for consistent results is easy, and fast.  Make sure the top is nailed first and hold the hanger flat against the face of the beam.  Since I Joists are consistent, a consistent install ensures a consistent plane.
.
.
Whenever possible, I install hangers to beams before lifting them in place.  This is much faster than ladder work later, and is much safer.
.
.
These are top flange ITS hangers from @strongtie and feature features the Strong-Grip™ seat and Funnel Flange™ design allowing standard joist installation without the use of joist nails, resulting in the lowest installed cost. Generally speaking, we don’t need web stiffeners, but when they are required, 2 .148” x 1 ½” nails must be installed in optional joist nai holes for standard installation values.  
.

You can see the first video in my feed running all our chargers.  In video 2, you can see the unit running beam saws.  Now we come to what else we can use this power station for.  As a content creator, I don’t really ever take time off.  When I’m on vacation, I’m still shooting video, taking photos and editing both for YouTube and social media.  That means lots of battery charging when I’m out and about.  I can also use it to power appliances when the power is out.  
.

When you make the decision to potential buy something like this, look at it as a capital investment and make a list of all the different uses for it.  Then make the decision. For example, what would it cost you to not be able to work because the power is out at work?  Factor that into being able to work because you have “battery backup” so to speak.  This only happens for us about once a year and we’ve purchased tools accordingly.
.
.
